g.aria-label: "Port" selects which USB port is connected to the Arduino. If there are multiple, just try them all.
First, select the Arduino Nano ATmega328p preset. This will set the programmer and MCU.
Select the firmware HEX file to upload
Erase all existing EEPROM storage, just to be safe.
Press Program! This is what the log should look like when it's done

If your Arduino is burned with an up to date bootloader, use 115200 Baud rate. If your Arduino has an old bootloader, use 57600 instead. If you aren't sure, just try both. Most firmware will run fine with any bootloader, but the Clock firmware will only run correctly with a new bootloader.
